HW07 README.txt
------------------------------------------------
This is a java GUI application to connect, send message and tasks between client and server.


INSTRUCTION
------------------------------------------------
CLIENT:
1. Start the client GUI by running the ClientController.java file.

2. Enter the desired IP address of the remote server. The default value is your own IP address

3. Click the Connect button to connect with the remote server

4. Enter the message in the "Send msg to host" area, hit Enter to send the message to remote server

5. Enter the qualified task name in Add Task field, the options including:
	5.1 client.clientModel.task.PalinNum
		Check a positive number is a palindrome or not.
		Example:
		1, 12321, 55 are palindrome numbers.
		78, 9821, 32 are not palindrome numbers.
	
	5.2 client.clientModel.task.PerfectSqr
		Compute Perfect Square to a given number of digits
		Example:
		Given n = 12, return 3 because 12 = 4 + 4 + 4
		Given n = 13, return 2 because 13 = 4 + 9
	
	
	5.3 client.clientModel.task.ReverseVowels
		Takes a string as input and reverse only the vowels of a string.
		Example:
		Given s = "hello", return "holle"
	
	5.4 client.clientModel.task.ReverseWordsInString
		Given an input string, reverse the string word by word.
		Example:
		Given s = "red yellow blue", return "blue yellow red
	
	5.5 client.clientModel.task.Sqroot
		Task to compute and return the square root of the value.

6. "Add to lists" button
	A task name you entered in the text field will be added to the drop lists.

7. "Run Task" button
	A task with selected type which in the upper drop list can be ran.
	
8. "Combine Tasks" button
	User can combine the two selected tasks in upper and lower drop lists to a new task type.
	The new task contains all the feature from two original ones.    	 	

9. "Run Parameter"
	User can enter required parameter here to make the desired task.

10. Click the Quit button to exit the application.

SEVER:
1. Start the server GUI by running the ServerController.java file. 

2. Enter the message in the "Send msg to client" area, hit Enter to send the message to remote client

3. Messages and tasks sent by the client will be displayed in the display area.

4. Click the Quit button to exit the application.


